  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Problem-solving skill is an important competency that children need to develop across a range of contexts to facilitate their understanding, connecting, and using mathematical concepts.",
    "As a result, teachers are encouraged to develop children's problem-solving skills during their early years of children's education (Szabo et al., 2020).",
    "With the advancement of technology, artificial intelligence (AI) tools have emerged as a potential for assisting children to learn and teachers to teach problem-solving skills.",
    "AI-based systems have been used to support learning and teaching processes, especially in mathematics education.",
    "Studies have shown that using AI-based systems in mathematics education increased student learning outcomes, including developing problem skills (Hwang & Tu, 2021; Van Vaerenbergh & Pérez-Suay, 2022)."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "As a result, teachers are encouraged to develop children's problem-solving skills during their early years of children's education (Szabo et al., 2020).",
